title: Transcript of remarks by SFH at QMH
content_text:
p>
			Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for 
			Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, at Queen Mary Hospital today 
			(August 4): Reporter: (on the condition of the Secretary for Development, Mr 
			Paul Chan) Secretary for Food and Health: The Secretary for Development, Mr 
			Paul Chan, has sustained what we call a whiplash injury to the neck. 
			It is a very common injury in traffic accidents. During a traffic

It is a very common injury in traffic accidents. During a traffic 
			accident, since the trunk is protected by the seat belt, whereas the 
			head and the neck are not, the head will be swung into flexion or 
			extension and the cervical spine will also be swung into a different 
			shape. During this process, particularly during the extension, the 
			cervical spine may suffer from an injury. In the Secretary for 
			Development, Mr Paul Chan's case, I understand that he does not have

Development, Mr Paul Chan's case, I understand that he does not have 
			any signs and symptoms pertaining to neurological injury. He feels 
			severe pain around his neck right now, which is because of the fact 
			that the muscles surrounding the cervical spine will be thrown into 
			contraction in order to protect the cervical spine as well as the 
			spinal cord from injury. (Please also refer to the
			<a href="../../../../cn/press_and_publications/press/2013/press130804.htm">
